defaultOur “Mozal” aluminium smelter in Mozambique is a good illustration of how investments 
defaultby the natural resources industry 
defaultcan support broader economic development
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultI
defaultn 1998 Mozambique was emerging from 17 years of civil war
default and making the difficult transition to a market based economy.  The country was hampered by weak institutions, few people had the training to build or work at a plant like Mozal
default,
default and malaria was endemic.  
default&#xa0;
defaultDevelopment of the project was backed by 
defaultthe 
defaultMozambique
default government, the UK, 
defaultthe 
defaultEU and 
defaultthe 
defaultWor
defaultl
defaultd Bank to help:
default&#xa0;
defaultWith a budget of $1.2 billion, the project was the largest ever foreign investment 
defaultand largely achieved its goals. 
defaultMozambique is expected to become a middle income country 
defaultand has received substantial overseas investment in recent years. 
default&#xa0;
defaultMozal
default has made a significant contribution 
defaultto 
defaultthis progress. The smelter has 
defaultcontributed
default 3-6% of the country’s GDP each year.  It employs 1200 people and 600 contractors directly and contributes to indirect job creation of approximately 6500 people.  Thousands o
defaultf people have trained at Mozal 
defaultand 
default93% of its employees are from Mozambique. The government is a shareholder and receives a proportional share of dividends.
default&#xa0;
defaultLast year, 
defaultMozal
default spent approximately $460 million with local businesses, including over 150 small 
defaultsuppliers that were established with support from Mozlink – an enterprise development program implemented by BHP Billiton to help spread the benefits of development. 
default 
defaultThe construction of Mozal also supported the construction of new power lines bringing pow
defaulter from South Africa to Mozambique 
defaultproviding reliable power to
default the south of 
defaultthe country supporting development more broadly.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe company’s successful healthcare programs have reduced the incidence of malaria in the local community from over 85% to less than 6%; and cut the HIV infection rate from 19% to 5%.  
default&#xa0;
defaultIn addition, 
defaultThe Mozal Community Development Trust (MCDT) was establi
defaultshed by BHP Billiton in 2000 
defaultand
default has initiated roughly 200 projects, focusing on quality of life, increasing access to healthcare, clean water and sanitation and poverty alleviation.
